&+Lsurroundings only to find a barren and desolate landscape. You have arrived at
&+Lthe dreaded land of Niflheim - Realm of the dead. This is where the souls of
&+Lall those who died an honorless death dwell, those without the courage to clam
&+La place in Valhalla.

&+LAbruptly the air befor you seems to shift and fold and as the haze clears you
&+Lsee befor you a tall woman. Known as Hel, she is the ruler of this cursed
&+Lrealm. She looks upon you with false pity and says 'My poor friend. What have
&+Lyou gotten yourself into'. With a crocked smile she approaches you and reaches
&+Lout to touch you. Your senses scream for you to run but you are too enthralled
&+Lby her beauty. You begin to think that perhaps you where mistaken, but that
&+Lchanges as she lays her hand on your forehead. It's as if the curtain of night
&+Lhas been pulled over your eyes. A small bright light grows bigger and bigger
&+Luntil its painful gleam becomes too agonizing to stare at. You try to turn
&+Laway your gaze but you cannot. Your head explodes in pain and then no more...

&+LNow yet another soul can be found lost wandering this wasteland without hope
&+Lor prospects. Not until the world unfolds will you be set free.&n
